Despite all benefits, especially for mitigation purposes, there is still a gap of knowledge to understand the ideal level of shade cover and how shade trees may affect coffee meteorological variables inside the gradient of shading, especially considering low to moderate shade (30% or less). Previous studies reporting temperature decrease, cup quality, yield, coffee disease in shaded-grown coffee areas, normally assessed extreme treatment, including less than 15% or more than 70% of shading (
 Barradas and Fanjul 1986; 
 Morais et al., 2006; 
 Soto-Pinto et al., 2000).
